RACE.FOOTNOTES: BANDSLAMMER away well, shook clear early, continued clear on the turn and into the lane, kept to task to win convincinlgly. RUNAWAY WYWY broke in, stalked leader in the two path, had to alter toward the rail when RESTLESS RAMBLER shifted out, continued along the inside on the turn, no match for leader in the lane but kept to task to save second. AROUND THE DIAL stalked paced three wide on the backstretch, continued three wide on the turn, launched bid three wide, kept to task and gained on RUNAWAY WYWY and just missed second. RESTLESS RAMBLER stalked leader off the rail on the backstretch, continued two wide on the turn, entered lane in range and outfinished under urging. MONGOLIAN MOON bothered by outside rival at the start, quickly fell way back and lacked speed on the backstretch, made mild progress along the inside in the lane. NAZARE stalked pace four wide on the backstretch, continued four wide on the turn and failed to respond in the lane.

ENTRY.OWNER: Saratoga West Ortega Jr Alex and Ortega Vincent

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (QUARTER HORSE RACE 2 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 67. Claiming Purse 8000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since June 27 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $2,500 (Maiden And Claiming Races For $2,000 Or Less Not Conside red In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: QUIET FOREST vied for lead along the inside, continued along the inside on the turn, began to inch away late on the turn and edged away under a strong drive in the lane. PETE'S INFERNO settled off the pace on the backstretch, stayed off the rail heading into the turn, advanced on the turn in between rivals, kept to task in the lane and got up for second along the inside. AUNTIE BEV brushed and bothered by outside rival at the start, showed good speed to contend for the early lead, continued vying for lead two wide on the turn, entered lane in the three path, asked right handed mid stretch, drifted out and was outfinished. FOR MY BROTHER broke in and bothered AUNTIE BEV at the start, well placed and tracked duo along the inside, continued to save ground on the turn, and failed to produce a kick in the lane after a good trip. STARSHIP SKY off slow, quickly fell back and trailed on the backstretch, went to the rail, saved ground through the turn and made minimal progress in the lane. AROUSING LOVER away well, rider chose to lay off the pace in the three path, continued to be kept wide and failed to have any finish in the lane.

ENTRY.COMMENT: broke in, tracked duo inside, lacked needed kick
